Klaus Bittner (born October 23, 1938) is a German rower who competed for the Unified Team of Germany in the 1960 Summer Olympics and in the 1964 Summer Olympics. He was born in Grlitz. In 1960 he was a crew member of the German boat which won the gold medal in the eights competition. Four years later he won the silver medal as member of the German boat in the eights event. 
